31void test42()
32{
33 Procedure proc;
34 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
35 Value* const42 = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 42);
36 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), const42);
37
38 CHECK(compileAndRun<int>(proc) == 42);
39}

55void testLoadAcq42()
56{
57 Procedure proc;
58 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
59 int x = 42;
60 root->appendNewControlValue(
61 proc, Return, Origin(),
62 root->appendNew<MemoryValue>(
63 proc, Load, Int32, Origin(),
64 root->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), &x),
65 0, HeapRange(42), HeapRange(42)));
66
67 auto code = compileProc(proc);
68 if (isARM64())
69 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "lda");
70 CHECK(invoke<int>(*code) == 42);
71}

73void testLoadWithOffsetImpl(int32_t offset64, int32_t offset32)
74{
75 {
76 Procedure proc;
77 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
78 int64_t x = -42;
79 Value* base = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
80 root->appendNewControlValue(
81 proc, Return, Origin(),
82 root->appendNew<MemoryValue>(
83 proc, Load, Int64, Origin(),
84 base,
85 offset64));
86
87 char* address = reinterpret_cast<char*>(&x) - offset64;
88 CHECK(compileAndRun<int64_t>(proc, address) == -42);
89 }
90 {
91 Procedure proc;
92 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
93 int32_t x = -42;
94 Value* base = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
95 root->appendNewControlValue(
96 proc, Return, Origin(),
97 root->appendNew<MemoryValue>(
98 proc, Load, Int32, Origin(),
99 base,
100 offset32));
101
102 char* address = reinterpret_cast<char*>(&x) - offset32;
103 CHECK(compileAndRun<int32_t>(proc, address) == -42);
104 }
105}

144static void testBitXorTreeArgs(int64_t a, int64_t b)
145{
146 Procedure proc;
147 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
148 Value* argA = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
149 Value* argB = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
150 Value* node = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitXor, Origin(), argA, argB);
151 node = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitXor, Origin(), node, argB);
152 node = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitXor, Origin(), node, argA);
153 node = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitXor, Origin(), node, argB);
154 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin(), node);
155
156 CHECK_EQ(compileAndRun<int64_t>(proc, a, b), (((a ^ b) ^ b) ^ a) ^ b);
157}
158
159static void testBitXorTreeArgsEven(int64_t a, int64_t b)
160{
161 Procedure proc;
162 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
163 Value* argA = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
164 Value* argB = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
165 Value* node = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitXor, Origin(), argA, argB);
166 node = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitXor, Origin(), node, argB);
167 node = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitXor, Origin(), node, argA);
168 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin(), node);
169
170 CHECK_EQ(compileAndRun<int64_t>(proc, a, b), ((a ^ b) ^ b) ^ a);
171}

173static void testBitXorTreeArgImm(int64_t a, int64_t b)
174{
175 Procedure proc;
176 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
177 Value* argA = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
178 Value* immB = root->appendNew<Const64Value>(proc, Origin(), b);
179 Value* node = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitXor, Origin(), argA, immB);
180 node = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitXor, Origin(), argA, node);
181 node = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitXor, Origin(), argA, node);
182 node = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitXor, Origin(), immB, node);
183 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin(), node);
184
185 CHECK_EQ(compileAndRun<int64_t>(proc, a), b ^ (a ^ (a ^ (a ^ b))));
186}

188void testAddTreeArg32(int32_t a)
189{
190 Procedure proc;
191 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
192 Value* argA = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
193 argA = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(), argA);
194 Value* node = argA;
195 int32_t expectedResult = a;
196 for (unsigned i = 0; i < 20; ++i) {
197 Value* otherNode;
198 if (!(i % 3)) {
199 otherNode = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), i);
200 expectedResult += i;
201 } else {
202 otherNode = argA;
203 expectedResult += a;
204 }
205 node = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(), node, otherNode);
206 }
207 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin(), node);
208
209 CHECK_EQ(compileAndRun<int32_t>(proc, a), expectedResult);
210}
211
212void testMulTreeArg32(int32_t a)
213{
214 // Fibonacci-like expression tree with multiplication instead of addition.
215 // Verifies that we don't explode on heavily factored graphs.
216 Procedure proc;
217 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
218 Value* argA = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
219 argA = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(), argA);
220 Value* nodeA = argA;
221 Value* nodeB = argA;
222 int32_t expectedA = a, expectedResult = a;
223 for (unsigned i = 0; i < 20; ++i) {
224 Value* newNodeB = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Mul, Origin(), nodeA, nodeB);
225 nodeA = nodeB;
226 nodeB = newNodeB;
227 int32_t newExpectedResult = expectedA * expectedResult;
228 expectedA = expectedResult;
229 expectedResult = newExpectedResult;
230 }
231 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin(), nodeB);
232
233 CHECK_EQ(compileAndRun<int32_t>(proc, a), expectedResult);
234}

236static void testBitAndTreeArg32(int32_t a)
237{
238 Procedure proc;
239 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
240 Value* argA = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
241 argA = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(), argA);
242 Value* node = argA;
243 for (unsigned i = 0; i < 8; ++i) {
244 Value* constI = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), i | 42);
245 Value* newBitAnd = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), argA, constI);
246 node = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), node, newBitAnd);
247 }
248 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin(), node);
249
250 CHECK_EQ(compileAndRun<int32_t>(proc, a), a & 42);
251}

253static void testBitOrTreeArg32(int32_t a)
254{
255 Procedure proc;
256 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
257 Value* argA = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
258 argA = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(), argA);
259 Value* node = argA;
260 for (unsigned i = 0; i < 8; ++i) {
261 Value* constI = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), i);
262 Value* newBitAnd = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitOr, Origin(), argA, constI);
263 node = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitOr, Origin(), node, newBitAnd);
264 }
265 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin(), node);
266
267 CHECK_EQ(compileAndRun<int32_t>(proc, a), a | 7);
268}

354void testAddArgMem(int64_t a, int64_t b)
355{
356 Procedure proc;
357 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
358 Value* address = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
359 MemoryValue* load = root->appendNew<MemoryValue>(proc, Load, Int64, Origin(), address);
360 Value* result = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(),
361 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0),
362 load);
363 root->appendNew<MemoryValue>(proc, Store, Origin(), result, address);
364 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 0));
365
366 int64_t inputOutput = b;
367 CHECK(!compileAndRun<int64_t>(proc, a, &inputOutput));
368 CHECK(inputOutput == a + b);
369}

530void testAddLoadTwice()
531{
532 auto test = [&] () {
533 Procedure proc;
534 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
535 int32_t value = 42;
536 Value* load = root->appendNew<MemoryValue>(
537 proc, Load, Int32, Origin(),
538 root->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), &value));
539 root->appendNewControlValue(
540 proc, Return, Origin(),
541 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(), load, load));
542
543 auto code = compileProc(proc);
544 CHECK(invoke<int32_t>(*code) == 42 * 2);
545 };
546
547 test();
548}

614void testAddArgFloat(float a)
615{
616 Procedure proc;
617 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
618 Value* argument32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
619 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
620 Value* floatValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), argument32);
621 Value* result = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(), floatValue, floatValue);
622 Value* result32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), result);
623 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), result32);
624
625
626 CHECK(isIdentical(compileAndRun<int32_t>(proc, bitwise_cast<int32_t>(a)), bitwise_cast<int32_t>(a + a)));
627}

629void testAddArgsFloat(float a, float b)
630{
631 Procedure proc;
632 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
633 Value* argument1int32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
634 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
635 Value* argument2int32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
636 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1));
637 Value* floatValue1 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), argument1int32);
638 Value* floatValue2 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), argument2int32);
639 Value* result = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(), floatValue1, floatValue2);
640 Value* result32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), result);
641 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), result32);
642

739void testAddArgsFloatWithEffectfulDoubleConversion(float a, float b)
740{
741 Procedure proc;
742 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
743 Value* argument1int32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
744 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
745 Value* argument2int32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
746 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1));
747 Value* floatValue1 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), argument1int32);
748 Value* floatValue2 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), argument2int32);
749 Value* asDouble1 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, FloatToDouble, Origin(), floatValue1);
750 Value* asDouble2 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, FloatToDouble, Origin(), floatValue2);
751 Value* result = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(), asDouble1, asDouble2);
752 Value* floatResult = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, DoubleToFloat, Origin(), result);
753 Value* doubleAddress = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR2);
754 root->appendNew<MemoryValue>(proc, Store, Origin(), result, doubleAddress);
755 Value* result32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), floatResult);
756 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), result32);
757
758 double effect = 0;
759 CHECK(isIdentical(compileAndRun<int32_t>(proc, bitwise_cast<int32_t>(a), bitwise_cast<int32_t>(b), &effect), bitwise_cast<int32_t>(a + b)));
760 CHECK(isIdentical(effect, static_cast<double>(a) + static_cast<double>(b)));
761}

763void testAddMulMulArgs(int64_t a, int64_t b, int64_t c)
764{
765 // We want to check every possible ordering of arguments (to properly check every path in B3ReduceStrength):
766 // ((a * b) + (a * c))
767 // ((a * b) + (c * a))
768 // ((b * a) + (a * c))
769 // ((b * a) + (c * a))
770 for (int i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
771 Procedure proc;
772 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
773 Value* argA = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
774 Value* argB = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
775 Value* argC = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR2);
776 Value* mulAB = i & 2 ? root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Mul, Origin(), argA, argB)
777 : root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Mul, Origin(), argB, argA);
778 Value* mulAC = i & 1 ? root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Mul, Origin(), argA, argC)
779 : root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Mul, Origin(), argC, argA);
780 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin(),
781 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(),
782 mulAB,
783 mulAC));
784
785 CHECK_EQ(compileAndRun<int64_t>(proc, a, b, c), ((a * b) + (a * c)));
786 }
787}

802void testMulArgStore(int a)
803{
804 Procedure proc;
805 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
806
807 int mulSlot;
808 int valueSlot;
809
810 Value* value = root->appendNew<Value>(
811 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
812 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
813 Value* mul = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Mul, Origin(), value, value);
814
815 root->appendNew<MemoryValue>(
816 proc, Store, Origin(), value,
817 root->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), &valueSlot), 0);
818 root->appendNew<MemoryValue>(
819 proc, Store, Origin(), mul,
820 root->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), &mulSlot), 0);
821
822 root->appendNewControlValue(
823 proc, Return, Origin(), root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 0));
824
825 CHECK(!compileAndRun<int>(proc, a));
826 CHECK(mulSlot == a * a);
827 CHECK(valueSlot == a);
828}

1047void testMulAddSignExtend32ArgsLeft()
1048{
1049 // d = SExt32(n) * SExt32(m) + a
1050 Procedure proc;
1051 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
1052
1053 Value* nValue = root->appendNew<Value>(
1054 proc, SExt32, Origin(),
1055 root->appendNew<Value>(
1056 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
1057 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0)));
1058 Value* mValue = root->appendNew<Value>(
1059 proc, SExt32, Origin(),
1060 root->appendNew<Value>(
1061 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
1062 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1)));
1063 Value* aValue = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR2);
1064
1065 Value* mulValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Mul, Origin(), nValue, mValue);
1066 Value* addValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(), mulValue, aValue);
1067 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), addValue);
1068
1069 auto code = compileProc(proc);
1070 if (isARM64())
1071 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "smaddl");
1072
1073 for (auto n : int32Operands()) {
1074 for (auto m : int32Operands()) {
1075 for (auto a : int64Operands()) {
1076 int64_t lhs = invoke<int64_t>(*code, n.value, m.value, a.value);
1077 int64_t rhs = static_cast<int64_t>(n.value) * static_cast<int64_t>(m.value) + a.value;
1078 CHECK(lhs == rhs);
1079 }
1080 }
1081 }
1082}

1177void testMulSubArgsLeft()
1178{
1179 Procedure proc;
1180 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
1181
1182 Value* arg0 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
1183 Value* arg1 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
1184 Value* arg2 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR2);
1185 Value* multiplied = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Mul, Origin(), arg0, arg1);
1186 Value* subtracted = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Sub, Origin(), multiplied, arg2);
1187 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), subtracted);
1188
1189 auto code = compileProc(proc);
1190 if (isARM64())
1191 checkDoesNotUseInstruction(*code, "msub");
1192

1198 }

1283void testMulSubSignExtend32Args()
1284{
1285 // d = a - SExt32(n) * SExt32(m)
1286 Procedure proc;
1287 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
1288
1289 Value* aValue = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
1290 Value* nValue = root->appendNew<Value>(
1291 proc, SExt32, Origin(),
1292 root->appendNew<Value>(
1293 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
1294 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1)));
1295 Value* mValue = root->appendNew<Value>(
1296 proc, SExt32, Origin(),
1297 root->appendNew<Value>(
1298 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
1299 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR2)));
1300
1301 Value* mulValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Mul, Origin(), nValue, mValue);
1302 Value* subValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Sub, Origin(), aValue, mulValue);
1303 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), subValue);
1304
1305 auto code = compileProc(proc);
1306 if (isARM64())
1307 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "smsubl");
1308
1309 for (auto a : int64Operands()) {
1310 for (auto n : int32Operands()) {
1311 for (auto m : int32Operands()) {
1312 int64_t lhs = invoke<int64_t>(*code, a.value, n.value, m.value);
1313 int64_t rhs = a.value - static_cast<int64_t>(n.value) * static_cast<int64_t>(m.value);
1314 CHECK(lhs == rhs);
1315 }
1316 }
1317 }
1318}

1541void testMulArgsFloatWithEffectfulDoubleConversion(float a, float b)
1542{
1543 Procedure proc;
1544 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
1545 Value* argument1int32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
1546 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
1547 Value* argument2int32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
1548 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1));
1549 Value* floatValue1 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), argument1int32);
1550 Value* floatValue2 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), argument2int32);
1551 Value* asDouble1 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, FloatToDouble, Origin(), floatValue1);
1552 Value* asDouble2 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, FloatToDouble, Origin(), floatValue2);
1553 Value* result = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Mul, Origin(), asDouble1, asDouble2);
1554 Value* floatResult = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, DoubleToFloat, Origin(), result);
1555 Value* doubleMulress = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR2);
1556 root->appendNew<MemoryValue>(proc, Store, Origin(), result, doubleMulress);
1557 Value* result32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), floatResult);
1558 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), result32);
1559
1560 double effect = 0;
1561 CHECK(isIdentical(compileAndRun<int32_t>(proc, bitwise_cast<int32_t>(a), bitwise_cast<int32_t>(b), &effect), bitwise_cast<int32_t>(a * b)));
1562 CHECK(isIdentical(effect, static_cast<double>(a) * static_cast<double>(b)));
1563}

1879void testDivArgsFloatWithEffectfulDoubleConversion(float a, float b)
1880{
1881 Procedure proc;
1882 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
1883 Value* argument1int32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
1884 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
1885 Value* argument2int32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
1886 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1));
1887 Value* floatValue1 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), argument1int32);
1888 Value* floatValue2 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), argument2int32);
1889 Value* asDouble1 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, FloatToDouble, Origin(), floatValue1);
1890 Value* asDouble2 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, FloatToDouble, Origin(), floatValue2);
1891 Value* result = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Div, Origin(), asDouble1, asDouble2);
1892 Value* floatResult = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, DoubleToFloat, Origin(), result);
1893 Value* doubleDivress = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR2);
1894 root->appendNew<MemoryValue>(proc, Store, Origin(), result, doubleDivress);
1895 Value* result32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), floatResult);
1896 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), result32);
1897
1898 double effect = 0;
1899 CHECK(isIdentical(compileAndRun<int32_t>(proc, bitwise_cast<int32_t>(a), bitwise_cast<int32_t>(b), &effect), bitwise_cast<int32_t>(a / b)));
1900 CHECK(isIdentical(effect, static_cast<double>(a) / static_cast<double>(b)));
1901}

2364
2365void testSubMulMulArgs(int64_t a, int64_t b, int64_t c)
2366{
2367 // We want to check every possible ordering of arguments (to properly check every path in B3ReduceStrength):
2368 // ((a * b) - (a * c))
2369 // ((a * b) - (c * a))
2370 // ((b * a) - (a * c))
2371 // ((b * a) - (c * a))
2372 for (int i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
2373 Procedure proc;
2374 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
2375 Value* argA = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
2376 Value* argB = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
2377 Value* argC = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR2);
2378 Value* mulAB = i & 2 ? root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Mul, Origin(), argA, argB)
2379 : root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Mul, Origin(), argB, argA);
2380 Value* mulAC = i & 1 ? root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Mul, Origin(), argA, argC)
2381 : root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Mul, Origin(), argC, argA);
2382 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin(),
2383 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Sub, Origin(),
2384 mulAB,
2385 mulAC));
2386
2387 CHECK_EQ(compileAndRun<int64_t>(proc, a, b, c), ((a * b) - (a * c)));
2388 }
2389}

2590void testTernarySubInstructionSelection(B3::Opcode valueModifier, Type valueType, Air::Opcode expectedOpcode)
2591{
2592 Procedure proc;
2593 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
2594
2595 Value* left = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
2596 Value* right = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
2597
2598 if (valueModifier == Trunc) {
2599 left = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, valueModifier, valueType, Origin(), left);
2600 right = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, valueModifier, valueType, Origin(), right);
2601 }
2602
2603 root->appendNewControlValue(
2604 proc, Return, Origin(),
2605 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Sub, Origin(), left, right));
2606
2607 lowerToAirForTesting(proc);
2608
2609 auto block = proc.code()[0];
2610 unsigned numberOfSubInstructions = 0;
2611 for (auto instruction : *block) {
2612 if (instruction.kind.opcode == expectedOpcode) {
2613 CHECK_EQ(instruction.args.size(), 3ul);
2614 CHECK_EQ(instruction.args[0].kind(), Air::Arg::Tmp);
2615 CHECK_EQ(instruction.args[1].kind(), Air::Arg::Tmp);
2616 CHECK_EQ(instruction.args[2].kind(), Air::Arg::Tmp);
2617 numberOfSubInstructions++;
2618 }
2619 }
2620 CHECK_EQ(numberOfSubInstructions, 1ul);
2621}

2664
2665void testUbfx32ShiftAnd()
2666{
2667 // Test Pattern: (src >> lsb) & mask
2668 // where: mask = (1 << width) - 1
2669 if (JSC::Options::defaultB3OptLevel() < 2)
2670 return;
2671 uint32_t src = 0xffffffff;
2672 Vector<uint32_t> lsbs = { 1, 14, 30 };
2673 Vector<uint32_t> widths = { 30, 17, 1 };
2674
2675 auto test = [&] (uint32_t lsb, uint32_t mask) -> uint32_t {
2676 Procedure proc;
2677 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
2678
2679 Value* srcValue = root->appendNew<Value>(
2680 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
2681 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
2682 Value* lsbValue = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), lsb);
2683 Value* maskValue = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), mask);
2684
2685 Value* left = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, ZShr, Origin(), srcValue, lsbValue);
2686 root->appendNewControlValue(
2687 proc, Return, Origin(),
2688 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), left, maskValue));
2689
2690 auto code = compileProc(proc);
2691 if (isARM64())
2692 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "ubfx");
2693 return invoke<uint32_t>(*code, src);
2694 };
2695
2696 auto generateMask = [&] (uint32_t width) -> uint32_t {
2697 return (1U << width) - 1U;
2698 };
2699
2700 for (size_t i = 0; i < lsbs.size(); ++i) {
2701 uint32_t lsb = lsbs.at(i);
2702 uint32_t mask = generateMask(widths.at(i));
2703 CHECK(test(lsb, mask) == ((src >> lsb) & mask));
2704 }
2705}
2706
2707void testUbfx32AndShift()
2708{
2709 // Test Pattern: mask & (src >> lsb)
2710 // Where: mask = (1 << width) - 1
2711 if (JSC::Options::defaultB3OptLevel() < 2)
2712 return;
2713 uint32_t src = 0xffffffff;
2714 Vector<uint32_t> lsbs = { 1, 14, 30 };
2715 Vector<uint32_t> widths = { 30, 17, 1 };
2716
2717 auto test = [&] (uint32_t lsb, uint32_t mask) -> uint32_t {
2718 Procedure proc;
2719 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
2720
2721 Value* srcValue = root->appendNew<Value>(
2722 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
2723 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
2724 Value* lsbValue = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), lsb);
2725 Value* maskValue = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), mask);
2726
2727 Value* right = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, ZShr, Origin(), srcValue, lsbValue);
2728 root->appendNewControlValue(
2729 proc, Return, Origin(),
2730 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), maskValue, right));
2731
2732 auto code = compileProc(proc);
2733 if (isARM64())
2734 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "ubfx");
2735 return invoke<uint32_t>(*code, src);
2736 };
2737
2738 auto generateMask = [&] (uint32_t width) -> uint32_t {
2739 return (1U << width) - 1U;
2740 };
2741
2742 for (size_t i = 0; i < lsbs.size(); ++i) {

3161void testInsertBitField32()
3162{
3163 if (!JSC::Options::useBFI())
3164 return;
3165 if (JSC::Options::defaultB3OptLevel() < 2)
3166 return;
3167 uint32_t d = 0xf0f0f0f0;
3168 uint32_t n = 0xffffffff;
3169 Vector<uint32_t> lsbs = { 2, 2, 14, 30, 30 };
3170 Vector<uint32_t> widths = { 30, 3, 17, 1, 2 };
3171
3172 // Test Pattern: d = ((n & mask1) << lsb) | (d & mask2)
3173 // Where: mask1 = ((1 << width) - 1)
3174 // mask2 = ~(mask1 << lsb)
3175 auto test1 = [&] (uint32_t lsb, uint32_t mask1, uint32_t mask2) -> uint32_t {
3176 Procedure proc;
3177 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
3178
3179 Value* dValue = root->appendNew<Value>(
3180 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
3181 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
3182 Value* nValue = root->appendNew<Value>(
3183 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
3184 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1));
3185 Value* lsbValue = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), lsb);
3186 Value* maskValue1 = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), mask1);
3187 Value* maskValue2 = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), mask2);
3188
3189 Value* leftAndValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), nValue, maskValue1);
3190 Value* shiftValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Shl, Origin(), leftAndValue, lsbValue);
3191 Value* rightAndValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), dValue, maskValue2);
3192 root->appendNewControlValue(
3193 proc, Return, Origin(),
3194 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitOr, Origin(), shiftValue, rightAndValue));
3195
3196 auto code = compileProc(proc);
3197 if (isARM64())
3198 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "bfi");
3199 return invoke<uint32_t>(*code, d, n);
3200 };
3201
3202 // Test Pattern: d = (d & mask2) | ((n & mask1) << lsb)
3203 // Where: mask1 = ((1 << width) - 1)
3204 // mask2 = ~(mask1 << lsb)
3205 auto test2 = [&] (uint32_t lsb, uint32_t mask1, uint32_t mask2) -> uint32_t {
3206 Procedure proc;
3207 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
3208
3209 Value* dValue = root->appendNew<Value>(
3210 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
3211 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
3212 Value* nValue = root->appendNew<Value>(
3213 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
3214 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1));
3215 Value* lsbValue = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), lsb);
3216 Value* maskValue1 = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), mask1);
3217 Value* maskValue2 = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), mask2);
3218
3219 Value* leftAndValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), dValue, maskValue2);
3220 Value* rightAndValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), nValue, maskValue1);
3221 Value* shiftValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Shl, Origin(), rightAndValue, lsbValue);
3222 root->appendNewControlValue(
3223 proc, Return, Origin(),
3224 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitOr, Origin(), leftAndValue, shiftValue));
3225
3226 auto code = compileProc(proc);
3227 if (isARM64())
3228 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "bfi");
3229 return invoke<uint32_t>(*code, d, n);
3230 };
3231
3232 for (size_t i = 0; i < lsbs.size(); ++i) {
3233 uint32_t lsb = lsbs.at(i);
3234 uint32_t mask1 = (1U << widths.at(i)) - 1U;
3235 uint32_t mask2 = ~(mask1 << lsb);
3236 CHECK(test1(lsb, mask1, mask2) == (((n & mask1) << lsb) | (d & mask2)));
3237 CHECK(test2(lsb, mask1, mask2) == ((d & mask2) | ((n & mask1) << lsb)));
3238 }
3239}

3285 Value* dValue = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
3286 Value* nValue = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
3287 Value* lsbValue = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), lsb);
3288 Value* maskValue1 = root->appendNew<Const64Value>(proc, Origin(), mask1);
3289 Value* maskValue2 = root->appendNew<Const64Value>(proc, Origin(), mask2);
3290
3291 Value* leftAndValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), dValue, maskValue2);
3292 Value* rightAndValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), nValue, maskValue1);
3293 Value* shiftValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Shl, Origin(), rightAndValue, lsbValue);
3294 root->appendNewControlValue(
3295 proc, Return, Origin(),
3296 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitOr, Origin(), leftAndValue, shiftValue));
3297
3298 auto code = compileProc(proc);
3299 if (isARM64())
3300 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "bfi");
3301 return invoke<uint64_t>(*code, d, n);
3302 };
3303
3304 for (size_t i = 0; i < lsbs.size(); ++i) {
3305 uint64_t lsb = lsbs.at(i);
3306 uint64_t mask1 = (1ULL << widths.at(i)) - 1ULL;
3307 uint64_t mask2 = ~(mask1 << lsb);
3308 CHECK(test1(lsb, mask1, mask2) == (((n & mask1) << lsb) | (d & mask2)));
3309 CHECK(test2(lsb, mask1, mask2) == ((d & mask2) | ((n & mask1) << lsb)));
3310 }
3311}

3313void testExtractInsertBitfieldAtLowEnd32()
3314{
3315 if (JSC::Options::defaultB3OptLevel() < 2)
3316 return;
3317 uint32_t d = 0xf0f0f0f0;
3318 uint32_t n = 0xffffffff;
3319 Vector<uint32_t> lsbs = { 1, 10, 14, 30 };
3320 Vector<uint32_t> widths = { 30, 11, 17, 1 };
3321
3322 // BFXIL Pattern: d = ((n >> lsb) & mask1) | (d & mask2)
3323 // Where: mask1 = ((1 << width) - 1)
3324 // mask2 = ~mask1
3325 auto test1 = [&] (uint32_t lsb, uint32_t mask1, uint32_t mask2) -> uint32_t {
3326 Procedure proc;
3327 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
3328
3329 Value* dValue = root->appendNew<Value>(
3330 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
3331 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
3332 Value* nValue = root->appendNew<Value>(
3333 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
3334 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1));
3335 Value* lsbValue = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), lsb);
3336 Value* maskValue1 = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), mask1);
3337 Value* maskValue2 = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), mask2);
3338
3339 Value* shiftValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, ZShr, Origin(), nValue, lsbValue);
3340 Value* leftAndValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), shiftValue, maskValue1);
3341 Value* rightAndValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), dValue, maskValue2);
3342 root->appendNewControlValue(
3343 proc, Return, Origin(),
3344 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitOr, Origin(), leftAndValue, rightAndValue));
3345
3346 auto code = compileProc(proc);
3347 if (isARM64())
3348 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "bfxil");
3349 return invoke<uint32_t>(*code, d, n);
3350 };
3351
3352 for (size_t i = 0; i < lsbs.size(); ++i) {
3353 uint32_t lsb = lsbs.at(i);
3354 uint32_t mask1 = (1U << widths.at(i)) - 1U;
3355 uint32_t mask2 = ~mask1;
3356 CHECK(test1(lsb, mask1, mask2) == (((n >> lsb) & mask1) | (d & mask2)));
3357 }
3358
3359 // BFXIL Pattern: d = ((n & mask1) >> lsb) | (d & mask2)
3360 // Where: mask1 = ((1 << width) - 1) << lsb
3361 // mask2 = ~(mask1 >> lsb)
3362 auto test2 = [&] (uint32_t lsb, uint32_t mask1, uint32_t mask2) -> uint32_t {
3363 Procedure proc;
3364 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
3365
3366 Value* dValue = root->appendNew<Value>(
3367 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
3368 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
3369 Value* nValue = root->appendNew<Value>(
3370 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
3371 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1));
3372 Value* lsbValue = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), lsb);
3373 Value* maskValue1 = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), mask1);
3374 Value* maskValue2 = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), mask2);
3375
3376 Value* leftAndValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), nValue, maskValue1);
3377 Value* rightAndValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), dValue, maskValue2);
3378 Value* shiftValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, ZShr, Origin(), leftAndValue, lsbValue);
3379 root->appendNewControlValue(
3380 proc, Return, Origin(),
3381 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitOr, Origin(), shiftValue, rightAndValue));
3382
3383 auto code = compileProc(proc);
3384 if (isARM64())
3385 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "bfxil");
3386 return invoke<uint32_t>(*code, d, n);
3387 };
3388
3389 for (size_t i = 0; i < lsbs.size(); ++i) {
3390 uint32_t lsb = lsbs.at(i);
3391 uint32_t mask1 = ((1U << widths.at(i)) - 1U) << lsb;
3392 uint32_t mask2 = ~(mask1 >> lsb);
3393 CHECK(test2(lsb, mask1, mask2) == (((n & mask1) >> lsb) | (d & mask2)));
3394 }
3395}

3706void testBitfieldZeroExtend32()
3707{
3708 if (JSC::Options::defaultB3OptLevel() < 2)
3709 return;
3710 Vector<uint32_t> amounts = { 0, 14, 31 };
3711
3712 // Turn this: ZShr(Shl(n, amount)), amount)
3713 // Into this: BitAnd(n, mask)
3714 // Conditions:
3715 // 1. 0 <= amount < datasize
3716 // 2. width = datasize - amount
3717 // 3. mask is !(mask & (mask + 1)) where bitCount(mask) == width
3718 auto test = [&] (uint32_t n, uint32_t amount) -> uint32_t {
3719 Procedure proc;
3720 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
3721
3722 Value* nValue = root->appendNew<Value>(
3723 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
3724 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
3725 Value* amountValue = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), amount);
3726 Value* shlValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Shl, Origin(), nValue, amountValue);
3727 Value* zshrValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, ZShr, Origin(), shlValue, amountValue);
3728 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), zshrValue);
3729
3730 auto code = compileProc(proc);
3731 if (isARM64() && amount > 0)
3732 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "and");
3733 return invoke<uint32_t>(*code, n, amount);
3734 };
3735
3736 uint32_t datasize = CHAR_BIT * sizeof(uint32_t);
3737 for (auto nOperand : int32Operands()) {
3738 for (auto amount : amounts) {
3739 uint32_t n = nOperand.value;
3740 uint32_t width = datasize - amount;
3741 uint32_t mask = width == datasize ? std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max() : (1U << width) - 1U;
3742 uint32_t lhs = test(n, amount);
3743 uint32_t rhs = (n & mask);
3744 CHECK(lhs == rhs);
3745 }
3746 }
3747}

3784void testExtractRegister32()
3785{
3786 if (JSC::Options::defaultB3OptLevel() < 2)
3787 return;
3788 Vector<uint32_t> lowWidths = { 0, 17, 31 };
3789
3790 // Test Pattern: ((n & mask1) << highWidth) | ((m & mask2) >> lowWidth)
3791 // Where: highWidth = datasize - lowWidth
3792 // mask1 = (1 << lowWidth) - 1
3793 // mask2 = ~mask1
3794 auto test = [&] (uint32_t n, uint32_t m, uint32_t mask1, uint32_t mask2, uint32_t highWidth, uint32_t lowWidth) -> uint32_t {
3795 Procedure proc;
3796 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
3797
3798 Value* nValue = root->appendNew<Value>(
3799 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
3800 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
3801 Value* mValue = root->appendNew<Value>(
3802 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
3803 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1));
3804 Value* mask1Value = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), mask1);
3805 Value* mask2Value = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), mask2);
3806 Value* highWidthValue = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), highWidth);
3807 Value* lowWidthValue = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), lowWidth);
3808
3809 Value* leftAndValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), nValue, mask1Value);
3810 Value* left = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Shl, Origin(), leftAndValue, highWidthValue);
3811
3812 Value* rightAndValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), mValue, mask2Value);
3813 Value* right = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, ZShr, Origin(), rightAndValue, lowWidthValue);
3814
3815 root->appendNewControlValue(
3816 proc, Return, Origin(),
3817 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitOr, Origin(), left, right));
3818
3819 auto code = compileProc(proc);
3820 if (isARM64() && lowWidth > 0)
3821 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "extr");
3822 return invoke<uint32_t>(*code, n, m);
3823 };
3824
3825 uint32_t datasize = CHAR_BIT * sizeof(uint32_t);
3826 for (auto nOperand : int32Operands()) {
3827 for (auto mOperand : int32Operands()) {
3828 for (auto lowWidth : lowWidths) {
3829 uint32_t n = nOperand.value;
3830 uint32_t m = mOperand.value;
3831 uint32_t highWidth = datasize - lowWidth;
3832 uint32_t mask1 = (1U << lowWidth) - 1U;
3833 uint32_t mask2 = ~mask1;
3834 uint32_t left = highWidth == datasize ? 0U : ((n & mask1) << highWidth);
3835 uint32_t right = ((m & mask2) >> lowWidth);
3836 uint32_t rhs = left | right;
3837 uint32_t lhs = test(n, m, mask1, mask2, highWidth, lowWidth);
3838 CHECK(lhs == rhs);
3839 }
3840 }
3841 }
3842}
3843
3844void testExtractRegister64()
3845{
3846 if (JSC::Options::defaultB3OptLevel() < 2)
3847 return;
3848 Vector<uint64_t> lowWidths = { 0, 34, 63 };
3849
3850 // Test Pattern: ((n & mask1) << highWidth) | ((m & mask2) >> lowWidth)
3851 // Where: highWidth = datasize - lowWidth
3852 // mask1 = (1 << lowWidth) - 1
3853 // mask2 = ~mask1
3854 auto test = [&] (uint64_t n, uint64_t m, uint64_t mask1, uint64_t mask2, uint64_t highWidth, uint64_t lowWidth) -> uint64_t {
3855 Procedure proc;
3856 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
3857
3858 Value* nValue = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
3859 Value* mValue = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
3860 Value* mask1Value = root->appendNew<Const64Value>(proc, Origin(), mask1);
3861 Value* mask2Value = root->appendNew<Const64Value>(proc, Origin(), mask2);
3862 Value* highWidthValue = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), highWidth);
3863 Value* lowWidthValue = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), lowWidth);
3864
3865 Value* leftAndValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), nValue, mask1Value);
3866 Value* left = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Shl, Origin(), leftAndValue, highWidthValue);
3867
3868 Value* rightAndValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), mValue, mask2Value);
3869 Value* right = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, ZShr, Origin(), rightAndValue, lowWidthValue);
3870
3871 root->appendNewControlValue(
3872 proc, Return, Origin(),
3873 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitOr, Origin(), left, right));
3874
3875 auto code = compileProc(proc);
3876 if (isARM64() && lowWidth > 0)
3877 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "extr");
3878 return invoke<uint64_t>(*code, n, m);
3879 };
3880
3881 uint64_t datasize = CHAR_BIT * sizeof(uint64_t);
3882 for (auto nOperand : int64Operands()) {
3883 for (auto mOperand : int64Operands()) {
3884 for (auto lowWidth : lowWidths) {
3885 uint64_t n = nOperand.value;
3886 uint64_t m = mOperand.value;
3887 uint64_t highWidth = datasize - lowWidth;
3888 uint64_t mask1 = (1ULL << lowWidth) - 1ULL;
3889 uint64_t mask2 = ~mask1;
3890 uint64_t left = highWidth == datasize ? 0ULL : ((n & mask1) << highWidth);
3891 uint64_t right = ((m & mask2) >> lowWidth);
3892 uint64_t rhs = left | right;
3893 uint64_t lhs = test(n, m, mask1, mask2, highWidth, lowWidth);
3894 CHECK(lhs == rhs);
3895 }
3896 }
3897 }
3898}

3900void testBitAndZeroShiftRightArgImmMask32()
3901{
3902 // Turn this: (tmp >> imm) & mask
3903 // Into this: tmp >> imm
3904 uint32_t tmp = 0xffffffff;
3905 Vector<uint32_t> imms = { 4, 28, 31 };
3906 Vector<uint32_t> masks = { 0x0fffffff, 0xf, 0xffff };
3907
3908 auto test = [&] (uint32_t imm, uint32_t mask) {
3909 Procedure proc;
3910 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
3911
3912 Value* tmpValue = root->appendNew<Value>(
3913 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
3914 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
3915 Value* immValue = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), imm);
3916 Value* leftValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, ZShr, Origin(), tmpValue, immValue);
3917 Value* rightValue = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), mask);
3918 root->appendNewControlValue(
3919 proc, Return, Origin(),
3920 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), leftValue, rightValue));
3921
3922 auto code = compileProc(proc);
3923 if (isARM64())
3924 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "lsr");
3925 uint32_t lhs = invoke<uint32_t>(*code, tmp);
3926 uint32_t rhs = tmp >> imm;
3927 CHECK(lhs == rhs);
3928 };
3929
3930 for (size_t i = 0; i < imms.size(); ++i)
3931 test(imms.at(i), masks.at(i));
3932}

4264{

4267 Value* arg0 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
4268 Value* arg1 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
4269 Value* equal = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Equal, Origin(), arg0, arg1);
4270 Value* maskedEqual = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(),
4271 root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 0x5),
4272 equal);
4273 Value* inverted = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitXor, Origin(),
4274 root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 0x1),
4275 maskedEqual);
4276 Value* select = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Select, Origin(), inverted,
4277 root->appendNew<Const64Value>(proc, Origin(), 42),
4278 root->appendNew<Const64Value>(proc, Origin(), -5));
4279
4280 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), select);
4281
4282 int64_t expected = (a == b) ? -5 : 42;
4283 CHECK(compileAndRun<int64_t>(proc, a, b) == expected);
4284}

4449static void testBitOrAndAndArgs(int64_t a, int64_t b, int64_t c)
4450{
4451 // We want to check every possible ordering of arguments (to properly check every path in B3ReduceStrength):
4452 // ((a & b) | (a & c))
4453 // ((a & b) | (c & a))
4454 // ((b & a) | (a & c))
4455 // ((b & a) | (c & a))
4456 for (int i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
4457 Procedure proc;
4458 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
4459 Value* argA = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
4460 Value* argB = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
4461 Value* argC = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR2);
4462 Value* andAB = i & 2 ? root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), argA, argB)
4463 : root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), argB, argA);
4464 Value* andAC = i & 1 ? root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), argA, argC)
4465 : root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), argC, argA);
4466 root->appendNewControlValue(
4467 proc, Return, Origin(),
4468 root->appendNew<Value>(
4469 proc, BitOr, Origin(),
4470 andAB,
4471 andAC));
4472
4473 CHECK_EQ(compileAndRun<int64_t>(proc, a, b, c), ((a & b) | (a & c)));
4474 }
4475}
